Pokémon Explorer
Overview
Pokémon Explorer is a simple web application that integrates with the Pokémon API to display data about Pokémon. The app features a grid layout of the first 50 Pokémon and provides a search functionality to find specific Pokémon by their name.

Features
Display Pokémon List: Shows the first 50 Pokémon with their names and images.
Search Pokémon: Allows users to search for a Pokémon by name.
Error Handling: Displays appropriate messages for:
API errors (e.g., failure to fetch data).
Pokémon not found when searching.
Technologies Used
Frontend:

HTML: Structure of the application.
CSS: Styling and layout.
JavaScript: API integration and dynamic content rendering.
API:
Pokémon API (https://pokeapi.co/docs/v2).

